### 9. Implementation Pitfall Analysis

**Identify variables/patterns that linters may flag incorrectly:**

In complex systems, certain patterns appear "unused" but are semantically critical:

| Pattern | Why It Looks Unused | Why It's Actually Needed |
|---------|---------------------|--------------------------|
| State variables | Not read in same scope | Needed by next loop iteration or external system |
| Tracking variables | Updated but not immediately read | Used by downstream aggregation or reporting |
| Correlation IDs | Assigned but not used locally | Passed to downstream systems for traceability |
| Flags/counters | Incremented but not read until loop end | Used for summary statistics |
